Reputation Hook Notes
=====================

Use SOCIETY_D->record_reputation_event() for new reputation changes.

Signature:
  record_reputation_event(player, heroism_delta, reason, source,
    hidden_dimensions, metadata)

Guidelines:
  * Guild membership alone should not move reputation.
  * Use actions: quests, rites, services, crimes, mercy, desecration,
    public praise, public harm, and other notable deeds.
  * Keep public heroism simple: positive trends Hero, negative trends
    Villain, zero stays Adventurer.
  * Put the "why" in hidden dimensions such as mercy, terror, honor,
    faith_mitra, faith_gaea, faith_set, nature, crime, secrecy, blood,
    service, community, and notoriety.
  * Use metadata["key"] plus metadata["repeat_cap"] for anything that
    must not be farmed repeatedly.

Quest objects may opt in with:
  mapping query_reputation_event(object player)

or:
  mixed *query_reputation_events(object player)

Each returned event mapping can contain:
  "heroism"    signed public heroism delta
  "reason"     short admin-facing reason
  "dimensions" hidden dimension deltas
  "metadata"   optional event metadata

The new quest daemon records quest reputation once per quest event.
